    document.getElementById("langs-text-aboutmetitle1").innerHTML = `How I started`
    document.getElementById("langs-text-aboutmetext1").innerHTML = `I first began to develop my current interests when I was about 9 years old. I used to play games on my phone, and I thought that it would be fun to try making my own, so I signed up for a local game programming course. We developed various simple games in basic programming languages like Dark Basic Pro and App Game Kit, later Python or C++, and we also worked on the games' visuals.`
    document.getElementById("langs-text-aboutmetext2").innerHTML = `After some time, I also tried developing 3D games, which I quite enjoyed, but it was much more difficult than the 2D games I worked on previously, even if the game itself was really simple. A big problem with the simple tools and basic programming languages was that there was no way to edit the levels visually, so everything had to be coded manually. I wanted a better solution. After searching for something and asking around, I discovered Unreal Engine. It looked great, so I downloaded it and started experimenting with it. Over time, I learned a lot about real-time 3D visuals used in games, as well as 3D computer graphics in general.`
    document.getElementById("langs-text-aboutmetext3").innerHTML = `While I worked on games, I also signed up for a web development course that caught my interest. Initially, we covered HTML and CSS, later we continued with JavaScript and I even tried PHP, React and SCSS. I realized that I enjoy designing websites more than coding, however, I found coding skills useful as well, and I kept working on them. It allowed me to make my own functional websites just like this one.`
    document.getElementById("langs-text-aboutmetitle2").innerHTML = `My current work`
    document.getElementById("langs-text-aboutmetext4").innerHTML = `Most of the projects I worked on over the recent years were primarily focused on 3D graphics and UX/UI Design, and I also built my portfolio website with that in mind. The majority of them do not perfectly fit under these two categories though. Each project has its own dedicated page containing more details. Coding projects currently do not have a separate category here and they will usually also be listed under graphics. Those that do not involve graphics will only be available on my GitHub. There is a separate photography page, which is currently work in progress and only accessible by search.`
    document.getElementById("langs-text-aboutmetext4-2").innerHTML = `Besides projects for real clients, my portfolio also includes my personal projects that I often work on in my free time. Their primary purpose is learning new skills and software, while also improving in what I already know.`
    document.getElementById("langs-text-aboutmetext4-3").innerHTML = `As a supporter of open source software, I often like to make use of such tools in my projects and I also use Fedora Linux as my primary system. However, I have no problem with using industry standard software as well, which I still work with most of the time.`
    document.getElementById("langs-text-aboutmetitle3").innerHTML = `What's next`
    document.getElementById("langs-text-aboutmetext5").innerHTML = `Currently I'm looking to focus mainly on 3D graphics and/or UX/UI design, but I'd also like to improve in all of the other areas I mention here on my portfolio, including programming, photography and some other related fields. I realize it's quite a broad range of skills to focus on, but only more experience can allow me to make the correct decision about what I'm going to specialize in and focus my career on. Moreover, making this decision deosn't force me to abandon my other interests.`
    document.getElementById("langs-text-aboutmetext5-2").innerHTML = `Progress in the digital landscape is also as fast as it's ever been, which strongly influences the job market. My skills and portfolio will have to adapt. I'm always open to learning something new and expanding my skillset. If you'd like to find out more about me and my work, feel free to keep looking around and check out the 3D and 2D Graphics pages.`
