        document.getElementById("langs-text-aboutmetitle1").innerHTML = `How I started`
        document.getElementById("langs-text-aboutmetext1").innerHTML = `I first began to develop my current interests when I was about 9 years old. I used to play games on my phone, and I thought that it would be fun to try making my own, so I signed up for a local game programming course. We developed various simple games in basic programming languages like Dark Basic Pro and App Game Kit, later Python or C++, and we also worked on the games' visuals.`
        document.getElementById("langs-text-aboutmetext2").innerHTML = `After some time, I also tried developing 3D games, which I quite enjoyed, but it was much more difficult than the 2D games I worked on previously, even if the game itself was really simple. A big problem with the simple tools and basic programming languages was that there was no way to edit the levels visually, so everything had to be coded manually. I wanted a better solution. After searching for something and asking around, I discovered Unreal Engine. It looked great, so I downloaded it and started experimenting with it. Over time, I learned a lot about real-time 3D visuals used in games, as well as 3D computer graphics in general.`
        document.getElementById("langs-text-aboutmetext3").innerHTML = `While I worked on games, I also signed up for a web development course that caught my interest. Initially, we covered HTML and CSS, later we continued with JavaScript and I even tried PHP, React and SCSS. I realized that I enjoy designing websites more than coding, however, I found coding skills useful as well, and I kept working on them. It allowed me to make my own functional websites just like this one.`
        document.getElementById("langs-text-aboutmetitle2").innerHTML = `My current work`
